				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Plane of Hate, Fear, Sky<a name="55433"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 6 04 10:23 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Although Hate has been redone, if you know your way around and don't go trying to tackle anything past tier 2 without some big guns, you'll be fine. Almost all the new maps I've seen for revamped hate have the tiers seperated and they can be a pain to read but once you're in there and have a looksie, you'll get used to what's what. The new Hate is one of my favorite zones now, I take friends there all the time and a group of us (mostly 60ish-65) can lock down 4 or 5 named and stay well ahead of the spawn rate. Pay close attention to which Placeholders bring which minis and named, and you'll be all set. Some guildies hold down the harder minis all the time for epic work but they're mostly elemental geared and have much more experience than I do in Hate. You can really have some fun here with friends and the loot is awesome. 
<br />
   Fear is truly a pushover, just don't go loose cannon and be careful of the ginantically humungous aggro ranges and don't kill the scarelings. 
<br />
   I honestly haven't been to Sky in over a year but the last time I was there we cleared to the third island (maybe, this is defenitely foggy in my memory here) without a problem and then got wiped with a single group of mostly 55-60ish folks. 
<br />

<br />
These are some of my favorite zones, I really like going because we spend so much time in PoP and everything, I miss the nostalgia and the fun of these cool scary places. Check out PoM too with a single group of 65s you can do a lot inside the castly, just make sure you read up before you take friends there so you don't fall in the fake bridge and stuff like that. Stay away from Growth unless you have at least 2 groups due to zonewide aggro on those d*mn protectors. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
